"title": "1320: God, as Saviour",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1320",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God is the only Saviour and deliverer of his people. His work of salvation is inaugurated in the OT, and reaches its climax in the work of Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>God is the only Saviour</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:21-Isa45:22\">ISA 45:21–45:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg10:13-Judg10:14\">JDG 10:13–10:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:11\">ISA 43:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:28\">JER 2:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:23\">JER 3:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:12\">JER 11:12</a></p>\n<h2>God's deliverance can be worked through a human agent</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:16\">JDG 2:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:5-Gen45:7\">GEN 45:5–45:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:10\">EXO 3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:6-Josh10:10\">JOS 10:6–10:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:18\">JDG 2:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:14-Judg6:16\">JDG 6:14–6:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs13:5\">2KI 13:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:1\">ISA 45:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:13\">ISA 45:13</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of God's saving deeds</h2>\n<p>God delivers his people from Egypt:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:6-Exod6:7\">EXO 6:6–6:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:13-Exod14:14\">EXO 14:13–14:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:21-Exod14:23\">EXO 14:21–14:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:27-Exod14:28\">EXO 14:27–14:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps77:19-Ps77:20\">PSA 77:19–77:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos13:4\">HOS 13:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:37\">1SA 17:37</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:1-2Sam22:3\">2SA 22:1–22:3</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:2\">PSA 18:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:18\">2SA 22:18</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:17\">PSA 18:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps3:8\">PSA 3:8</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:16-Dan6:22\">DAN 6:16–6:22</a> <em>God delivers Daniel from the lions' den.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:18-Acts5:19\">ACT 5:18–5:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:6-Acts12:11\">ACT 12:6–12:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:25-Acts16:26\">ACT 16:25–16:26</a></p>\n<h2>God's acts of deliverance reveal his nature and character</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:10\">ISA 52:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps98:2\">PSA 98:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:6\">ISA 49:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:4-Luke3:6\">LUK 3:4–3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:3-Isa40:5\">ISA 40:3–40:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:16\">ROM 1:16</a></p>\n<h3>His strength is seen</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:2\">PSA 18:2</a></strong> <em>“rock” and “horn” symbolise God's strength; they are fequently used to emphasise his ability to save.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:2\">EXO 15:2</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps118:14\">PSA 118:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:1\">1SA 2:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:2-2Sam22:3\">2SA 22:2–22:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:47\">2SA 22:47</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:46\">PSA 18:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps28:8\">PSA 28:8</a></p>\n<h3>His glory is seen</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:4\">EXO 14:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:17-Exod14:18\">EXO 14:17–14:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:22\">NUM 14:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps85:9\">PSA 85:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:19\">ISA 66:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek39:21\">EZK 39:21</a></p>\n<h2>God's deliverance is anticipated</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:2\">PSA 31:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:18\">GEN 49:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:4\">PSA 35:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:13-Ps69:15\">PSA 69:13–69:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa33:22\">ISA 33:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:4\">ISA 35:4</a></p>\n<h2>God's deliverance is promised</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:6\">EXO 6:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps50:15\">PSA 50:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps91:14\">PSA 91:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa38:6\">ISA 38:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:4\">ISA 46:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:12\">EZK 34:12</a></p>\n<h2>Implications of God's deliverance for believers</h2>\n<h3>God is able to deliver believers from trials and testing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:18\">2TI 4:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan12:1\">DAN 12:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:13\">MAT 6:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:13\">1CO 10:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:9\">2PE 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:10\">REV 3:10</a></p>\n<h3>God is able to deliver believers from sin and death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:24-Rom7:25\">ROM 7:24–7:25</a></strong> <em>God delivers both from death owing to adversity and from death that comes about as a result of sin.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:13\">2SA 12:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:19\">PSA 33:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:23\">EZK 37:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:56-1Cor15:57\">1CO 15:56–15:57</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:9-2Cor1:10\">2CO 1:9–1:10</a></p>\n<h2>Testimony to God as Saviour and deliverer</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:20\">GEN 50:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps13:5\">PSA 13:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:46-Ps18:48\">PSA 18:46–18:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:10\">ISA 61:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:27\">DAN 6:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:18\">HAB 3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:47\">LUK 1:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:10\">1TI 4:10</a></p>",
